The first-ever BRICS Games have been concluded in Guangzhou, China, with SA bringing home a medal.All the BRICS countries - Brazil, Russia, India, China and South Africa - took part in three sporting codes, namely basketball, volleyball and wushu (martial arts form) involving almost 300 athletes competing. The SA basketball side managed to win a bronze medal against India with an 88-75 victory. They arrived in the country yesterday.